Question : can we modify a collection without crating a copy in java??
Solution : Yes, it is possible to modify a collection in Java without creating a copy, provided that the collection itself is mutable.
        
        import java.util.ArrayList;
        import java.util.List;
        
        public class CollectionModification {
            public static void main(String[] args) {
                List<String> originalList = new ArrayList<>();
                originalList.add("Apple");
                originalList.add("Banana");
        
                // Modify the collection directly
                originalList.add("Cherry"); 
                originalList.remove("Apple");
        
                System.out.println(originalList); // Output: [Banana, Cherry]
            }
        }
